Abstract = {Unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) has been widely applied in
   internet-of-things (IoT) scenarios while the security for UAV
   communications remains a challenging problem due to the broadcast nature
   of the line-of-sight (LoS) wireless channels. This article investigates
   the security problems for dual UAV-assisted mobile edge computing (MEC)
   systems, where one UAV is invoked to help the ground terminal devices
   (TDs) to compute the offloaded tasks and the other one acts as a jammer
   to suppress the vicious eavesdroppers. In our framework, minimum secure
   computing capacity maximization problems are proposed for both the time
   division multiple access (TDMA) scheme and non-orthogonal multiple
   access (NOMA) scheme by jointly optimizing the communication resources,
   computation resources, and UAVs' trajectories. The formulated problems
