Abstract = {As the general mobile edge computing (MEC) scheme cannot adequately
   handle the emergency communication requirements in vehicular networks,
   unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-assisted vehicular edge computing networks
   (VECNs) are envisioned as the reliable and cost-efficient paradigm for
   the mobility and flexibility of UAVs. UAVs can perform as the temporary
   base stations to provide edge services for road vehicles with heavy
   traffic. However, it takes a long time and huge energy consumption for
   the UAV to fly from the stay charging station to the mission areas
   disorderly. In this paper, we design a pre-dispatch UAV-assisted VECNs
