Month = {SEP},
Abstract = {Positioning services in cellular networks are at risk of being abused by
   unauthorized users, which may severely damage the interests of operators
   and legitimate users. In this letter, multiple unmanned aerial vehicles
   (UAVs) are employed as mobile jammers to disrupt the positioning
   services at unauthorized users, thereby enhancing the controllability of
   services at the physical layer. Specifically, we aim to jointly optimize
   the UAVs' locations and jamming power to maximize the minimum position
   error of unauthorized users, while ensuring that the needs of legitimate
   users are met. To solve this non-convex optimization problem, an
